data.title: NJN News; Monday January 27, 1997
data.meta_description:
Full 6:00pm News cast with Kent Manahan; State treasury wants to collect
more taxes from pizza parlors, cleanup for leaky underground storage tanks,
North Jersey woman bogged down in red tape to get new wheelchair, Barbara
Bissell ordered to begin prison sentence, Thomas Smith Jr. sworn in as first
African American Superior court judge, triple murder suicide in Vineland,
hold up in transfer of accused child killers Amy Grossberg and Brian
Peterson, New NJ traffic information system, deer dangers increasing along
highways, Gov. Whitman joins Jersey Devils in introducing kids to street
hockey at Brookdale School, Middle School students in Marlton show off
science projects.
